Docker Commands for Your K8s SaaS Project

Run these from your project root:

~/k8s-saas

(where docker-compose.yml exists)

✅ 1. Stop Existing Containers
docker-compose down
Remove volumes too (optional clean reset)
docker-compose down -v
✅ 2. Build Fresh Images
docker-compose build
Build without cache (recommended after code changes)
docker-compose build --no-cache
✅ 3. Start Containers
Detached mode (recommended)
docker-compose up -d
Build + start together
docker-compose up --build -d
✅ 4. View Running Containers
docker ps
✅ 5. View Logs
All services
docker-compose logs -f
Backend only
docker-compose logs -f backend
Frontend only
docker-compose logs -f frontend
✅ 6. Restart Services
All
docker-compose restart
Backend only
docker-compose restart backend
Frontend only
docker-compose restart frontend
✅ 7. Enter Container Shell
Backend
docker exec -it k8s-backend bash

(If bash missing:)

docker exec -it k8s-backend sh
Frontend
docker exec -it k8s-frontend sh
✅ 8. Remove Everything + Rebuild Clean
docker-compose down -v
docker system prune -af
docker-compose up --build -d
🚀 Recommended Daily Workflow

After updating main.py or App.jsx:

docker-compose down
docker-compose up --build -d
